{"questionId":"11362","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The speed of a spaceship is measured to be 0.50<em>c</em> by an observer at rest in the Earth’s reference frame.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Define an <em>inertial reference frame.</em></span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">a coordinate system which is not accelerating/has constant velocity/Newtons 1st law applies ✔</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">OWTTE</span></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Both “inertial” and “reference frame” need to be defined</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11362","referenceCode":"19M.3.SL.TZ2.4ai","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Define an inertial reference frame.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"ai","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)","A.1 – The beginnings of relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}